==English==
===Noun Phrase===
'''the writing on the wall'''

# An [[ominous]] warning; a [[prediction]] of bad luck.
#: ''He could see the '''writing on the wall''' months before the business failed.''

===Etymology===
From the [[biblical]] story in the [[w:Book of Daniel|Book of Daniel]]; mysterious writing on the wall during King Belshazzar's feast points to the downfall of the Babylonian Empire.